(1648, 554, 'yes', 'greenbullet.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you understand the factors that impact sales. There are many factors that impact sales such as :&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">type and number of customers&nbsp;</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">cost of supplies</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">marketing&nbsp;</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">other outside forces</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '4', 'Factors Impacting Sales'),
(1649, 554, 'no', 'redbullet.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you do not understand the factors that impact sales. There are many factors that impact sales such as :&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">type and number of customers&nbsp;</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">cost of supplies</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">marketing&nbsp;</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">other outside forces</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '1', 'Factors Impacting Sales'),
(1650, 555, 'Company Positioning ', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#33cc00\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&bull;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">When we asked you to identify the sales strategies you employ, you selected company positioning. Company positioning indicates&nbsp;that you recognize the importance of your brand and where it stands in relation to other competitors in the market place.</span></span></p>\r\n', '2', 'Nil'),
(1651, 555, 'Product positioning \r\n', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#33cc00\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&bull;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">When we asked you to identify the sales strategies you employ, you selected Product positioning as one of the strategies. Product positioning shows your understanding of how your product set compares with that of your&nbsp;competitors and whether your messaging indicates that you are selling a premium product or pursuing low-cost leadership.</span></span></p>\r\n', '2', 'Nil'),
(1652, 555, 'Price setting\r\n', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#33cc00\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&bull;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">When we asked you to identify the sales strategies you employ, you selected Price setting as one of the strategies.&nbsp;A pricing strategy is a model or method used to establish the best price for a product or service.&nbsp;It helps you choose prices to maximize profits and shareholder value while considering consumer and market demand.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n', '2', 'Nil'),
(1653, 555, 'Choosing effective distribution channels ', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#33cc00\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&bull;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">When we asked you to identify the sales strategies you employ, you selected Choosing effective distribution channels as one of the strategies.&nbsp;Choosing effective distribution channels indicates your understanding that you cannot sell your products in every channel and therefore,&nbsp;you focus on choosing a small number of channels that offer you the best way to market and the maximum return.</span></span></p>\r\n', '2', 'Nil'),
(1654, 555, 'Adopting effective sales techniques ', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#33cc00\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&bull;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">When we asked you to identify the sales strategies you employ, you selected Adopting effective sales techniques as one of the strategies.&nbsp;The most effective sales techniques involve understanding your customers and solving a problem for them. The best way to do this involves empathic&nbsp;listening; mirroring what your customer is saying and delivering real value at a reasonable price.</span></span></p>\r\n', '2', 'Nil'),
(1655, 555, 'None of the Above', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#e74c3c\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&bull;</span></span></span><span style=\"color:#33cc00\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Since you are not using any of the strategies listed, I suggest you to carefully analyze all the options and identify which of the sales strategies would be&nbsp;most beneficial for your business. Once you have identified the strategy you need to implement the same. In case you find it difficult to identify, you can get in touch with any of our experts who can assist you in this.</span></span></p>\r\n', '0', 'Nil'),
(1656, 556, 'CEO', 'yellowbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You selected &ldquo;CEO&rdquo; as who do selling in your business. There is no right or wrong answer to this question. The real question is how effective is your sales effort? If your&nbsp;sales effort only requires a single individual to give you outstanding results, then that is fine. However, if you use everyone in your sales effort and still only get mediocre results, then your sales function needs remedial action to get it working properly. The simple message is to go with whatever works effectively for your business.</span></span></p>\r\n', '3.8', 'Who Do Selling'),
(1657, 556, 'Dedicated Sales Team', 'yellowbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You selected &ldquo;Dedicated Sales Team&rdquo; as who do selling in your business. There is no right or wrong answer to this question. The real question is how effective is your sales effort? If your sales effort only requires a single individual to give you outstanding results, then that is fine. However, if yo use&nbsp;everyone in your sales effort and still only get mediocre results, then your sales function needs remedial action to get it working properly. The simple message is to go with whatever works effectively for your business.</span></span></p>\r\n', '3.9', 'Who Do Selling'),
(1658, 556, 'Individual Sales Person', 'yellowbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You selected &ldquo;Individual Sales person&rdquo; as who do selling in your business. There is no right or wrong answer to this question. The real question is how effective is your sales effort? If your sales effort only requires a single individual to give you outstanding results, then that is fine. However, if you use everyone in your sales effort and still only get mediocre results, then your sales function needs remedial action to get it working properly. The simple message is to go with whatever works effectively for your business.</span></span></p>\r\n', '4', 'Who Do Selling'),
(1659, 556, 'Marketing People', 'yellowbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You selected &ldquo;Marketing people&rdquo; as who do selling in your business. There is no right or wrong answer to this question. The real question is how effective is your sales effort? If your sales effort only requires a single individual to give you outstanding results, then that is fine. However, if you use everyone in your sales effort and still only get mediocre results, then your sales function needs remedial action to get it working properly. The simple message is to go with whatever works effectively for your business.</span></span></p>\r\n', '4', 'Who Do Selling'),
(1660, 556, 'Any Two or More', 'yellowbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You selected &ldquo;two or more&rdquo; out of &quot;CEO&quot;, &quot;Dedicated Sales Team&quot; &quot;Individual Sales Person&quot; &quot;Marketing People&quot; as who do selling in your business. There is no right or wrong answer to this question. The real question is how effective is your sales effort? If your sales effort only requires a single individual to give you outstanding results, then that is fine. However, if you use everyone in your sales effort and still only get mediocre results, then your sales function needs remedial action to get it working properly. The simple message is to go with whatever works effectively for your business.</span></span></p>\r\n', '4', 'Who Do Selling'),
(1661, 557, 'Above Average', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">It is a positive sign that your sales staff is above average. However, you should not be satisfied by this and should always be on the look out for improvement opportunities so that the staff gets better day by day.</span></span></p>\r\n', '8', 'Effectiveness of Sales Staff'),
(1662, 557, 'Average', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Since your staff is average, you need to find out the reason for the same. You need to set up a system to constantly train your sales team. Further you need to equip them with necessary tool kit in the form of sales pitch, how to handle objections etc.</span></span></p>\r\n', '2', 'Effectiveness of Sales Staff'),
(1663, 557, 'Below Average', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Since your staff is average, you need to find out the reason for the same. You need to set up a system to constantly train your sales team. Further you need to equip them with necessary tool kit in the form of sales pitch, how to handle objections etc.</span></span></p>\r\n', '2', 'Effectiveness of Sales Staff');
INSERT INTO `options` (`id`, `question_id`, `options`, `option_bullet`, `option_answer`, `option_point`, `option_header`) VALUES
(1664, 558, 'yes', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you have an effective system for identifying and managing your business pipeline. This is necessary as it gives the following benefits:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Forecast Sales Accurately</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Recognize Aggregate Sales Velocity</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Monitor a Team&rsquo;s Progress</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Stimulate Resource Allocation</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Nurture Leads</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '8', 'Business Pipeline'),
(1665, 558, 'no', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you have an effective system for identifying and managing your business pipeline. This is necessary as it gives the following benefits:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Forecast Sales Accurately</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Recognize Aggregate Sales Velocity</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Monitor a Team&rsquo;s Progress</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Stimulate Resource Allocation</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Nurture Leads</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '2', 'Business Pipeline'),
(1666, 559, 'Growing', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You indicated that your sales turnover is growing. However, this should not make you complacent. You need to analyze your growth in light of industry growth rate,&nbsp;growth rates of companies similar in size and location. Further, you should strive for becoming the fastest growing company in your industry. &nbsp;In case you feel you can grow at faster rate but unable to do so, you can get in touch with us and we will help you to achieve exponential growth.</span></span></p>\r\n', '8', 'Turnover'),
(1667, 559, 'Stable', 'yellowbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You indicated that your sales turnover is stable.&nbsp; If your sales are increasing below the rate of inflation, or worse, are static, then you need to find out why and then act quickly. Look for practical ways to build sales and identify areas of business growth and chase these targets or markets. If you are not able to do this, you&rsquo;ll need to find ways to cut your costs in order to remain profitable. Few action points in this regard:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Spend some time analyzing where your sales have traditionally come from and what is blocking more sales from these sources. Meet with your advisory team and get their input. Hold an emergency meeting with staff or other stakeholders (such as suppliers) to plan what other markets you can target.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Identify where you can diversify.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Identify if you can sell other products and services to your existing customer base.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Investigate if there are any pockets of demand that you may have ignored in the past as being too small, that are now increasingly attractive in your search for sales.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Consider forming joint ventures with other businesses or developing new distribution channels.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Hold a meeting and inform all staff that you have set increases to achieve&nbsp;or the business will need to consider a restructure. Pass on some responsibility for sales to&nbsp;everyone in your business. They need to understand you&#39;re all in it together. Think about how you are going to motivate, incentivize, reward and thank staff.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Set a realistic monthly sales-growth target to start you on the way to recovery. Share this with your staff to gain their buy-in.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Provide an incentive for sales people if they hit and exceed targets, such as a percentage of the additional profit gained from exceeding monthly target</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Implement monthly sales reports to compare sales with last year</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Identify industries that are growing and then plan to promote or advertise to these sectors that still have budgets.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Further, you can get in touch with us and we will help you to achieve exponential growth</span></span></p>\r\n', '4', 'Turnover'),
(1668, 559, 'Declining', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You indicated that your sales turnover is declining. &nbsp;If your sales are increasing below the rate of inflation, or worse, are static, then you need to find out why and then act quickly. Look for practical ways to build sales and identify areas of business growth and chase these targets or markets. If you are not able to do this, you will need to find ways to cut your costs in order to remain profitable. Few action points in this regard:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Spend some time analyzing where your sales have traditionally come from and what is blocking more sales from these sources. Meet with your advisory team and get their input. Hold an emergency meeting with staff or other stakeholders (such as suppliers) to plan what other markets you can target.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Identify where you can diversify.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Identify if you can sell other products and services to your existing customer base.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Investigate if there are any pockets of demand that you may have ignored in the past as being too small, that are now increasingly attractive in your search for sales.&nbsp;</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Consider forming joint ventures with other businesses or developing new distribution channels.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Hold a meeting and inform all staff that you have set increases to achieve or the business will need to consider a restructure. Pass on some responsibility for sales to everyone in your business. They need to understand you are all in it together. Think about how you are going to motivate, incentivize, reward and thank staff.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Set a realistic monthly sales-growth target to start you on the way to recovery. Share this with your staff to gain their buy-in.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Provide an incentive for sales people if they hit and exceed targets, such as a percentage of the additional profit gained from exceeding monthly targets.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Implement monthly sales reports to compare sales with last year.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Identify industries that are growing and then plan to promote or advertise to these sectors that still have budgets.&nbsp;</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Further, you can get in touch with us and we will help you to achieve exponential growth.</span></span></p>\r\n', '4', 'Turnover'),
(1669, 560, 'yes', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you have an adequate sales support. It is essential to have as it gives the following benefits:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">makes it easier to find and attract your target customers</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">better manage customer relationship</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">improve your sales team performance</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '5', 'Sales Support'),
(1670, 560, 'no', 'redbullet.png', '<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You mentioned that you do not have an adequate sales support. It is essential to have as it gives the following benefits:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">makes it easier to find and attract your target customers</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">better manage customer relationship</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">improve your sales team performance</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '1', 'Sales Support'),
(1671, 561, 'Current Market Rate', 'yellowbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you pay as per industry norms. This is fine as long as you are able to do the following:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Attract top talent</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Retain key employees</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Reward long-serving employees</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Reward good performance</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Reduce theft of employees</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '3', 'Salary to Sales Staff'),
(1672, 561, 'More than Industry Rate', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You indicated that you pay more than industry rate. This is good provided you get the following benefits:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Attract top talent</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Retain key employees</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Reward long-serving employees</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Reward good performance</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Reduce theft of employees</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '5', 'Salary to Sales Staff'),
(1673, 561, 'Less than Industry Rate', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You indicated that you pay less than industry rate. You might need to change that in case you are facing the following challenges:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Not able to attract top talent</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Unable to retain key employees</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Unable to reward long serving employees</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Unable to reward good performance</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Increase theft &nbsp;of employees</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '1', 'Salary to Sales Staff'),
(1674, 562, 'yes', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that there is a commission structure in place to reward sales staff. It is good as it:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Encourages employees to work harder</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Helps manage payroll expenses</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '4', ''),
(1675, 562, 'no', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&nbsp;You mentioned that there is no commission structure in place to reward sales staff. You should put the same in place as it</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Encourages employees to work harder</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Helps manage payroll expenses</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '0', ''),
(1676, 563, 'yes', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You mentioned that you do not have an accurate understanding of cost of acquisition of a customer. It is essential that you price your products so that the lifetime value of profit from a customer consistently exceeds the cost of servicing him, plus the cost of acquiring the customer in the first place. &nbsp;<strong>Customer acquisition cost </strong>(CAC) is a common metric for determining how effective your customer acquisition activities are. It can be used to calculate the marketing cost per customer acquired over a period of time or for a particular marketing approach. This information can be used to assess the overall success of your acquisition operations. It can also assist in determining which techniques are yielding the best results. Dividing marketing costs by the number of consumers obtained is a typical method for calculating customer acquisition costs.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n', '1', 'Customer Acquisition Cost'),
(1677, 563, 'no', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you have an accurate understanding of cost of acquisition of a customer. It is essential to know the cost of acquisition of a customer. It is essential that you price your products so that the lifetime value of profit from a customer consistently exceeds the cost of servicing him, plus the cost of acquiring the customer in the first place. <strong>Customer acquisition cost </strong>(CAC) is a common metric for determining how effective your customer acquisition activities are. It can be used to calculate the marketing cost per customer acquired over a period of time or for a particular marketing approach. This information can be used to assess the overall success of your acquisition operations. It can also assist in determining which techniques are yielding the best results. Dividing marketing costs by the number of consumers obtained is a typical method for calculating customer acquisition costs.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n', '5', 'Customer Acquisition Cost'),
(1680, 565, 'yes', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you have an accurate understanding of cost of acquisition of a customer. It is essential that you price your products so that the lifetime value of profit from a customer consistently exceeds the cost of servicing him, plus the cost of acquiring the customer in the first place. Here&rsquo;s how to do it:<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&bull;</span></span><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&nbsp;To calculate Lifetime Value of a Customer, you need to take the gross margin you make from the customer over their lifetime, and subtract all direct support and operational expenses. Knowing CLV has the following benefits:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">CLV allows you to measure the financial impact of marketing campaigns, initiatives, and other activities.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">CLV can also change the way you think about marketing in terms of creating loyalty objectives or focusing spend on underutilized areas.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">CLV will help you find balance in terms of short-term and long-term marketing goals and demonstrate a better understanding of financial return on your investments.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">CLV encourages better decision making by teaching marketers to spend less time acquiring customers with lower value.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '5', 'Lifetime Value of Customer'),
(1681, 565, 'no', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you do not have an accurate understanding of cost of acquisition of a customer. It is essential that you price your products so that the lifetime value of profit from a customer consistently exceeds the cost of servicing him, plus the cost of acquiring the customer in the first place. Here&rsquo;s how to do:&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&bull;</span></span><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&nbsp;To calculate Lifetime Value of a Customer, you need to take the gross margin you make from the customer over their lifetime, and subtract all direct support and operational expenses.&nbsp;Knowing CLV has the following benefits:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">CLV allows you to measure the financial impact of marketing campaigns, initiatives, and other activities.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">CLV can also change the way you think about marketing in terms of creating loyalty objectives or focusing spend on underutilized areas.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">CLV will help you find balance in terms of short-term and long-term marketing goals and demonstrate a better understanding of financial return on your investments.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">CLV encourages better decision making by teaching marketers to spend less time acquiring customers with lower value.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '0', 'Lifetime Value of Customer'),
(1682, 566, 'yes', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you have a clear understanding of how much revenue each employee generates. &nbsp;This is a useful metric to have. Compare this with employee cost to reveal if each employee is making a positive financial contribution to your business or if some are just extra baggage that you may need to shed.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n', '5', 'Revenue Per Employee'),
(1683, 566, 'no', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you do not have a clear understanding of how much revenue each employee generates. &nbsp;It is easier to figure this out for sales staff than it is for customer service or other support people. So start with the sales people and once you have your numbers calculated for them, then you can go on to assess economic value generated by support people. At the end of the day, each employee must generate sufficient revenue or value to cover their full cost.</span></span></p>\r\n', '0', 'Revenue Per Employee'),
(1684, 567, 'yes', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You mentioned that you do factor in the time and cost of granting credit and collecting receivables when quoting a price. &nbsp;This should be coupled with the analysis of lifetime value of a customer versus the cost of acquiring a customer.</span></span></p>\r\n', '5', 'Costing'),
(1685, 567, 'no', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You mentioned that you do not factor in the time and cost of granting credit and collecting receivables when quoting a price. Maybe you should look closer at this to ascertain if you are making a realistic and sustainable profit on high value sales. Financing costs for inventory and receivables can eat into margins to such an extent that there is no longer an economic return on a sale. This should be coupled with the analysis of lifetime value of a customer versus the cost of acquiring a customer.</span></span></p>\r\n', '0', 'Costing'),
(1686, 568, 'Above average', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You mentioned that the quality and consistency of your sales process is above average. This assumes that you have seen other sales processes and that the one used in your current business is superior. If this is the case, that&rsquo;s awesome.</span></span></p>\r\n', '7', 'Effectiveness of Sales Staff'),
(1687, 568, 'Average', 'yellowbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You mentioned that the quality and consistency of your sales process is average. Sales is the engine room that generates the cash that pays for everything else, so it is really important that you design the sales process to consistently maximise the results it achieves. If there are elements of the process that need revision or tweaking, you need to do this right now.</span></span></p>\r\n', '4', 'Effectiveness of Sales Staff'),
(1688, 568, 'Below Average', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You mentioned that the quality and consistency of your sales process is below average. You need to quickly identify why this is the case. You need to figure out why your sales process is not delivering for you and replace it with one that works. Sometimes the best place to look is amongst your competitors. What are they doing and how are they doing it? It&rsquo;s a lot easier to copy a successful wheel design and implement it than to go out and try to redesign it completely.</span></span></p>\r\n', '1', 'Effectiveness of Sales Staff'),
(1689, 569, 'yes', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you are happy with your record of obtaining regular new referrals from existing customers. Great. It is a lot easier to turn a referral into a new customer than to go out and find a new one that knows nothing about you or your business. Referrals by their nature are already open to doing business with you so you do not need to employ hard sell tactics. An important word here is &ldquo;regular&rdquo;. Getting a onetime referral from a customer can be useful. However, getting a stream of regular referrals from existing customers can be transformative for your business.</span></span></p>\r\n', '7', 'Referrals from Existing Customers'),
(1690, 569, 'no', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You mentioned that you are unhappy with your record of obtaining regular new referrals from existing customers. So why do you not get more referrals from customers. Sometimes it can be because you simply do not ask your customers to make a referral or recommendation. If your customers have a pleasant experience with your business, they will often be ready to make regular referrals if you just ask them to do so. On the other hand, if customers have a poor experience with your business, then they are not going to refer anyone. Therefore, find the underlying cause of why you do not get enough customer referrals by asking customers would they be prepared to recommend you or not. Their response will dictate the action you need to take.a</span></span></p>\r\n', '2', 'Referrals from Existing Customers'),
(1691, 570, 'yes', 'greenbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">You mentioned that you have an active and engaging digital presence. Being online can help attract new customers for your business. It can also increase how many customers you can reach, improve your customer communication and build customer loyalty. Before you start using any of these online channels, review the different options and see which is the best fit for&nbsp; your business.&nbsp;An active digital presence may include:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Websites</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Social Media</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Payment or booking platforms</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Email Marketing</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '10', 'Digital Presence'),
(1692, 570, 'no', 'redbullet.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You mentioned that you do not have an active and engaging digital presence. Being online can help attract new customers for your business. It can also increase how many customers you can reach, improve your customer communication and build customer loyalty. Before you start using any of these online channels, review the different options and see which is the best fit for your business. An active digital presence may include:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Websites</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Social Media</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Payment or booking platforms</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Email Marketing</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '2', 'Digital Presence');
